You've given us this land and this community in which we live.

24:59.288 --> 25:03.513
You've given us the witness of your church that celebrates your birth around the world.

25:04.894 --> 25:11.122
Today we are especially grateful for the gift of your son who gave up his heavenly home for a manger and a cross

25:11.234 --> 25:15.700
so that we might experience redemption and give that neither spoils nor fades.

25:16.721 --> 25:22.729
With the angels, we also desire peace on earth, a peace that is broader and deeper than the end of war.

25:23.951 --> 25:31.261
And we pray for restoration of this world, for the growth of your kingdom, for reconciliation, for healing, and for renewal.

25:32.282 --> 25:38.290
We bring before you our prayers for the countries of this world, especially for those at war.

25:42.050 --> 25:45.273
We pray for our country and for those who are in authority.

25:49.237 --> 25:53.161
We pray for our state and the local community and those who lead us.

25:57.505 --> 26:02.090
And Lord, we pray for the Universal Church, its mission and all those who minister.

26:06.574 --> 26:10.258
We pray to you for local congregations in Midland and their ministries.

26:10.786 --> 26:19.578
God at Midland Reform Church, we want to learn to live and love like Jesus, your Son, our Lord, and proclaim His name and word indeed in our community.

26:20.099 --> 26:22.562
Bless us with your spirit to do so faithfully.

26:24.625 --> 26:27.709
The Lord, we lift up to you the specific needs of our congregation.

26:28.610 --> 26:40.146
By name we pray for Joey Hinton, K. Bolander, Melody Dirks, Wayne Johnson, all those that are in need who are suffering physical illness or awaiting surgeries,

26:41.154 --> 26:43.197
God, we ask that you would be with the Shafer family.

26:43.958 --> 26:50.488
Thank you that yesterday, they were able to grieve Jerry's death, celebrate the life that he now has with you.

26:50.528 --> 26:55.315
May they continue to find hope and comfort in the promises of your word.

26:56.436 --> 27:00.102
Give especially K strength for the days, the weeks, and the years ahead.

27:00.142 --> 27:08.594
God, we ask that you would be with those who are unable to worship with us, those who are alone this time of the year,

27:09.346 --> 27:15.934
and for those who suffer in silence.

27:15.954 --> 27:19.920
Oh Lord Jesus Christ, you are our light, you are our hope.

27:21.842 --> 27:30.473
We pray that you would give us the strength, give us the boldness, give us the compassion to know and see the darkness of the world and to bring your light into it.

27:31.875 --> 27:34.258
We pray these things in Christ's name, amen.

